    "body": "### Problem\n\nOn the latest build `NVIM v0.11.0-dev-1457+g43d552c566` with [grug-far](https://github.com/MagicDuck/grug-far.nvim) plugin I got crash with message:\n```log\nnvim: /home/runner/work/neovim/neovim/src/nvim/decoration.c:979: buf_signcols_count_range: Assertion `buf->b_signcols.count[prevwidth - 1] >= 0' failed.\n```\nVideo:\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ddbe7ece-4302-4ece-9447-dd2a0617cb0c\nI edited simple file with following content:\n```txt\nline1\n\nline2\n\nline2\n\nline1\n\nline1\n\nline2\n\n```\nIt crashes when I press \\r to replace entries, then \\f to refresh plugin\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim file.txt\ninput: \n```txt\nline1\n\nline2\n\nline2\n\nline1\n\nline1\n\nline2\n\n```\n:GrugFar\nFind line1 entries\nSet replace to 'content'\nExclude first entry from search results\n\\r\n\\f\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo crash\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-1457+g43d552c566\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11/24H2 (WSL debian bookworm)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom github releases",
